nodes.bodyText:
An alternative could be to have a localDateFromStartOfTimeAndSecondsOffset() function which may then be used for mapping to a ServiceDate (commit):
leg.serviceDate = new ServiceDate(localDateFromStartOfTimeAndSecondsOffset(startOfTime, ((TripScheduleWithOffset) tripSchedule).getSecondsOffset()));

public static LocalDate localDateFromStartOfTimeAndSecondsOffset(ZonedDateTime startOfTime, int secondsOffset) {
    ZonedDateTime noon = startOfTime.plusSeconds(secondsOffset).plusHours(12);
    return noon.toLocalDate();
}

Would this be preferable?
